## Instructions
1. Split each author name into `first_name` and `last_name`; keep `full_name` as-is.
2. Standardize affiliation names (e.g. "MIT" → "Massachusetts Institute of Technology").
3. Classify `affiliation_type` as one of: university, company, lab, government, or null.
4. Infer `affiliation_country` from the affiliation text when possible.
5. Set `orcid_mentioned` only if an ORCID appears in the source.
6. Infer `career_stage_inferred` from affiliation and context (e.g. "PhD student", "Professor", "Researcher").
7. Return null for fields that cannot be confidently inferred.

